  "title": "Project Quantity Surveyor (Architectural Works / West Region)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities: </strong></p><ul><li>Monitor and control project costs for MRT station projects to ensure budget compliance.</li><li>Prepare and analyze cost comparisons to identify cost-saving opportunities.</li><li>Obtain, evaluate, and negotiate quotations with subcontractors and suppliers.</li><li>Perform quantity take-offs and measurements for cost estimation and billing.</li><li>Prepare variation orders, claims, final accounts, and settlement documents.</li><li>Manage monthly progress claims, variations, and subcontractor payments.</li><li>Administer post-contract matters for main contracts and subcontracts.</li><li>Liaise with consultants, QS, architects, developers, contractors, and suppliers.</li><li>Source and recommend cost-effective materials in line with project requirements.</li><li>Prepare detailed financial reports in Mandarin for China head office.</li><li>Work independently with strong analytical skills and attention to detail.</li><li>Collaborate effectively as a team player to support project delivery.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements: </strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Building, Quantity Surveying, or Civil Engineering.</li><li>Minimum 5 years’ experience as a Quantity Surveyor with main construction companies.</li></ul><p><strong>______________________________________________________</strong></p><p><strong>HOW TO APPLY :</strong></p><p><strong>Interested candidates, please submit your resume by clicking on “Quick Apply” or contact win@hkmsvs.com for more details.</strong></p><p><strong>Please provide following information in the resume for immediate processing</strong></p><p><strong>1) Reasons for leaving current and/or last employment</strong></p><p><strong>2) Last drawn and/or current salary</strong></p><p><strong>3) Expected salary</strong></p><p><strong>4) Date of availability and/or Notice Period</strong></p><p><strong>All applications will be treated in strictest confidence and only shortlisted candidates will be notified</strong></p><p><strong>Wee Wai Dan</strong></p><p><strong>EA License No : 03C5391</strong></p><p><strong>EA Reg No : R22109628</strong></p>",
